verses.verse: A Song <S%H7892><s%> of degrees. <S%H4609><s%> I will lift <S%H5375><s%> up my eyes <S%H5869><s%> to the hills, <S%H2022><s%> from where <S%H370><s%> comes <S%H935><s%> my help. <S%H5828><s%>
My help <S%H5828><s%> comes from the LORD, <S%H3068><s%> which made <S%H6213><s%> heaven <S%H8064><s%> and earth. <S%H776><s%>
He will not suffer <S%H5414><s%> your foot <S%H7272><s%> to be moved: <S%H4132><s%> he that keeps <S%H8104><s%> you will not slumber. <S%H5123><s%>
Behold, <S%H2009><s%> he that keeps <S%H8104><s%> Israel <S%H3478><s%> shall neither <S%H3808><s%> slumber <S%H5123><s%> nor <S%H3808><s%> sleep. <S%H3462><s%>
The LORD <S%H3068><s%> is your keeper: <S%H8104><s%> the LORD <S%H3068><s%> is your shade <S%H6738><s%> on your right <S%H3225><s%> hand. <S%H3027><s%>
The sun <S%H8121><s%> shall not smite <S%H5221><s%> you by day, <S%H3119><s%> nor the moon <S%H3394><s%> by night. <S%H3915><s%>
The LORD <S%H3068><s%> shall preserve <S%H8104><s%> you from all <S%H3605><s%> evil: <S%H7451><s%> he shall preserve <S%H8104><s%> your soul. <S%H5315><s%>
The LORD <S%H3068><s%> shall preserve <S%H8104><s%> your going <S%H3318><s%> out and your coming <S%H935><s%> in from this time forth, and even for ever more. <S%H5769><s%>
